 <purpose>
   <p>
     This part of ISO 10303 specifies an application module for the
     identification and representation of a collection of product data.
   </p>
   <p>
     The product data could potentially be any data within the scope of the schema.
   </p>

 </purpose>

 <!-- Items in scope -->
 <inscope>
   <li>identification of a set of product data grouped together for a common purpose, such as sales/marketing, analysis, production, usage, support activity, support solution and disposal;</li>
   <li>identification of a collection as a subset of another collection; </li>
 </inscope>

 <!-- Items out of scope -->
 <outscope>
   <li>activities to be performed on the collection.</li>
 </outscope>

